     <font class="TallRed">Conversation with "D", another victim of the RIAA<a name="108693384698763004">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          <center>This post is to inform others the dangers of filesharing MP3s and how much the RIAA sucks. <br /><img src="http://tim.movementarian.com/archives/riaa-kittens.jpg"></center><br />The below dialog is REAL, cut and pasted from an AIM log. The person I'm speaking to went to my High School and has been an E3R reader for quite some time. His name has been changed to conceal his identity.<blockquote>me: "D", i heard what happened dude. RIAA sucks.<br />"D": yes they do<br />me: 3000$ out of court?<br />"D": yeah i'm just waiting to hear more at this point<br />"D": more or less, but about that<br />me: how many mp3s did you have?<br />"D": they've a list of 6 differernt songs uploaded from my dorm<br />me: so for 6 songs they're making you pay 3000$<br />"D": for a while i was thinking it was my roommate not me since he dl's more than i do, then i saw the list and i really don't think my roommate would have cure or smiths on his comp<br />"D": basically<br />"D": if i went to court they could charge me over $100000 per song if they wanted to<br />"D": which is why i'm settling<br />me: jesus<br />me: what P2P program were you running?<br />"D": kazaa<br />"D": the shadiest of the shady<br />me: yeah. wow. so when do you hear back from the RIAA?<br />"D": i'm not really sure<br />"D": june 1 was the date my school gave them my name and my roommates name<br />me: what did your parents say about all of this?<br />"D": lol my mom was pretty pissed<br />"D": since i was "breaking the law"<br />me: moms get blinded sometimes.<br />"D": she feels i kinda deserve what i'm getting<br />            01:41<br />me: did she ever copy a cassette for a friend of hers?<br />me: probably.<br />"D": maybe<br />"D": i've made my argument to her<br />"D": but, since its "illegal", to her i was in the wrong<br />me: whole thing is stupid. the only difference is they have a way to track down everything now.<br />me: ya<br />"D": its totally stupid<br />"D": they'd have to sue all the teens of america to truly get piracy to stop<br />"D": its a completely vain effort<br />me: i don't download music anymore. I haven't in like a couple years.<br />me: I still <strong>(INSERT NOT-SO-LEGAL ACTIVITY HERE)</strong> but no downloadin' music for me...no sir<br />"D": well i'm a music fiend and i've found the best way to discover new bands is to dl it<br />me: yeah many found that to be the best way<br />"D": but yeah theres no way in hell i'll dl illegally again, i wouldnt be surprised if RIAA keeps an eye on me for a few years</blockquote>There you have it folks. This is for the small number of you who just need to witness one of their close friends get whomped by the huge evil force, sweeping the country's colleges campuses and basements. We're fighting a losing battle when our privacy rights have been raped the way they have. No sense in fighting if we have no guns. Only time will heal this wound. <br /><br />This is FSEVN signing off.<br /><br />Good Morning, America.<br />
